    {
      "id": "402940eb77225c93b5475b3e34b0ea5d6c2c18b4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-27 10:35:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI checked osp_statfs() - it does return an error if the connection is not ready. so we should not be able to use disconnected OSP.\n\nI'd suggest to put something like LASSERT(d->opd_pre_ready == 0); at the beginning of osp_precreate_cleanup_orphans().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2b12c5f7608d4338ad5ee1c546caa2a849b7cc86",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-28 05:26:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nLooks pretty reasonable...  What needs to be done to finish this off, besides making a better commit comment?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "44b5338402c2624381279abfdea84be91ed52bcf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-28 07:12:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI might be wrong as this is not very obvious, but it seem the original implementation used hidden logic to block new creates:\n\n        d->opd_pre_next = body->oa.o_id + 1;\n        /* nothing precreated yet, the pool is empty */\n        d->opd_pre_last_created = d->opd_pre_next;\n\nIOW, the pool was made empty on orphan cleanup and only successful precreation turned it available.\n\nI think this case deserve a good description somewhere in the code, the sequence which turn just reconnected OSP into a good one, including all the contraints like \"no creations are available till that\", etc.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a9f1248dbb7dcf8e3befec136162bc740e98acb9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-11-30 15:49:21.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 4.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "deb23fd0df4b7d101a580ccbea19053eaf1cd61e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-11-30 15:51:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nPatch set 4 addresses Alex's comment on blocking new reservations _only_ during orphan recoveries, not immediately after disconnections.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "48e74405b484f39b3a970db35748e96153e7334d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-11-30 15:54:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nAnd, it also makes \"waiting for all existing reservations to go away\" more robust.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
